str2: Wherefore, on which account, therefore. From dia and hos; through which thing, i.e. Consequently.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: (a) I say, speak; I mean, mention, tell, (b) I call, name, especially in the pass., (c) I tell, command.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: To go up, mount, ascend; of things: I rise, spring up, come up. From ana and the base of basis; to go up.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
Height, heaven; dignity, eminence. From a derivative of huper; elevation, i.e. altitude, the sky, or dignity.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To take captive, captivate. From aichmalotos; to capture.
Captivity; a captive multitude. From aichmalotos; captivity.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To offer, give; I put, place. A prolonged form of a primary verb; to give.
A gift, present. From the base of didomi; a present.
A man, one of the human race. From aner and ops; man-faced, i.e. A human being.
